               <floruit source="#bibl1475-1" when="0396" syriaca-computed-start="0396">0396</floruit>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl1475-1">Simeon est fete par les Syriaques occidentaux le rer ou le 2 octobre, le 4, 13 ou 18 janvier. Nau, Notice, 8-18; BHO, 1120. Palmer, Monk and Mason, sommaire 15 et passim. BSO, II, 1030-31 (J.M. Fiey).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Simeon was known as the second founder of Qartmin. He was healed at a young age by Samuel of Qartmin, who also instructed him in monasticism. An angel led them to the place where they were to construct the monastery of Qartmin. He was the second abbot of Qartmin and blessed Rabbula of Edessa.</note>
